        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I can't give you exact figures but I can tell you what I've learned from experience.</P><P>ST seems to have a set duration of about 20 seconds or so.  It does not break early from what I've seen.  The problem is that it will not always make the MOB forget about you.  When I split a spawn with ST I usually cast ST on mob#1, cast dark and fear on mob#2 and then turn around and start watching the ST'd mob#1 to see what happens when ST wears off.  If ST wears off and he comes charging, I cast ST on him again and then turn around and cast a couple more spells on mob#2.</P><P>I have yet to try this but I hear it works...  If you cast ST on a MOB and then FD, he will forget about you when ST wears off.  So if this is true then you can ST mob#1, dark and fear mob#2 then FD.  Once ST wears off and mob#1 has forgotten about you you can stand up and continue killing mob#2.</P><P>I hope that makes sense.  Basically there is a set duration for ST but the memory wipe part of the spell does not always work.  As you get higher in level the memory wipe portion works less and less often.  I'm level 44 now and more than half of the mobs I ST do not forget about me.</P><P><BR>Insert witty comment and original artwork here.</P><P>Corto Muerte<BR>44 Gnecromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
