        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I'm currently hunting the druids/ranger on the hill in EC (lvl 34-37+ atm) and I have to use ST to bust them up. I've found sometimes if you st one, then dark and fear the other, he 2nd mob won't be far enough away from the first before ST wears off. In the case of a bad pull, I will skip the dark and just fear one. This makes the mob run off fast (these mob's have sow) and I have enough time to either kill or re-ST the first one. It took about 2 deaths to come up with this :) </P><P><BR>Davorak Cal'Quorteken</P><P>Causing nightmares for 34 Seasons</P><P>current gear:<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121605" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121605</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
